            <scopecontent id="aspace_fa60e9e5e52e36e2d76c549df96410cc">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series I, Correspondence, contains letters to Kathleen Foster Campbell from friends, many of whom were members of the University of Chicago Poetry Club. The bulk of the correspondence is from Janet Lewis. Third-party correspondence is comprised of letters to Gladys Campbell and Janet Lewis.</p>
               <p>A highlight of the series is letters to Campbell from Janet Lewis at Sunmount Sanitorium in Santa Fe, New Mexico during her recovery from tuberculosis. They describe Lewis's courtship with Arthur Yvor Winters and her slow recovery from illness. Included with an undated letter are holograph drafts of Lewis's poems, "To W.S.L.," "Song," "The Tennis Players," and "Napoleon at Elba."</p>
            </scopecontent>
